Heresy is distinct from both apostasy , which is the explicit renunciation of one 's religion , principles or cause , and blasphemy , which is an impious utterance or action concerning God or sacred things .
The term is usually used to refer to violations of important religious teachings , but is used also of views strongly opposed to any generally accepted ideas .
The Greek for the phrase `` divisive person '' became a technical term in the early Church for a type of `` heretic '' who promoted dissension .
Saint Peter of Antioch referred to Christians that refused to venerate religious images as having `` Jewish minds '' .
By this edict the state 's authority and that of the Church became somewhat overlapping .
The number of people executed as heretics under the authority of the various `` ecclesiastical authorities '' -LSB- note 1 -RSB- is not known .
But they will become greatly defiled and they will fall into the name of error and into the hands of an evil cunning man and a manifold dogma , and they will be ruled heretically '' .
The first one was that of Bogomils in modern day Bosnia , a sort of sanctuary between Eastern and Western Christianity .
He was required to `` abjure , curse and detest '' those opinions .
He labeled all heresy as `` Jewish '' , claiming that Judaism would `` pollute -LSB- Catholics and -RSB- deceive them with sacrilegious seduction . ''
Under Mary , around two hundred and ninety people were burned at the stake between 1555 and 1558 after the restoration of papal jurisdiction .
When Elizabeth I came to the throne , the concept of heresy was retained in theory but severely restricted by the 1559 Act of Supremacy and the one hundred and eighty or so Catholics who were executed in the forty-five years of her reign were put to death because they were considered members of '' ... a subversive fifth column . ''
Although the charge was technically one of `` blasphemy '' there was one later execution in Scotland -LRB- still at that date an entirely independent kingdom -RRB- when in 1697 Thomas Aikenhead was accused , among other things , of denying the doctrine of the Trinity .
As such , most of Orthodox Judaism considers Reform and Reconstructionist Judaism heretical movements , and regards most of Conservative Judaism as heretical .
mentioning religious , political , socioeconomic and scientific heresies .
Characteristics were ascribed to both and examples of both kinds were offered .
He acknowledged by examples that heresy has repeatedly become orthodoxy .
