Pubs hold special events , from tournaments of the aforementioned games to karaoke nights to pub quizzes .
Some pubs in the UK also have football teams composed of regular customers .
Pubs may be venues for pub songs and live music .
In South East England -LRB- especially London -RRB- it was common until recent times for vendors selling cockles , whelks , mussels , and other shellfish to sell to customers during the evening and at closing time .
Quality dropped but variety increased with the introduction of microwave ovens and freezer food .
In addition , dishes such as burgers , chicken wings , lasagne and chilli con carne are often served .
Some pubs offer elaborate hot and cold snacks free to customers at Sunday lunchtimes , to prevent them getting hungry and leaving for their lunch at home .
A gastropub concentrates on quality food .
The concept of a restaurant in a pub reinvigorated both pub culture and British dining , though has occasionally attracted criticism for potentially removing the character of traditional pubs .
