The term `` Christian '' is also used adjectivally to describe anything associated with Christianity , or in a proverbial sense `` all that is noble , and good , and Christ-like . ''
By 2050 , the Christian population is expected to exceed 3 billion .
Today , about 37 % of all Christians live in the Americas , and about 26 % live in Europe , 24 % of total Christians live in sub-Saharan Africa , about 13 % in Asia and the Pacific , and 1 % of the world 's Christians live in the Middle east and North Africa .
Orthodox communions comprise 12 % of the world 's Christians .
Other Christian groups make up the remainder .
280 million Christian live as a minority .
In the Greek Septuagint , christos was used to translate the Hebrew מָשִׁיחַ -LRB- Mašíaḥ , messiah -RRB- , meaning '' -LSB- one who is -RSB- anointed . ''
