In some countries Nasrani tends to be used generically for non-Muslim Western foreigners , e.g. `` blond people . ''
The region of modern Eastern Europe and Central Eurasia -LRB- Russia , Ukraine and other countries of the ex-USSR -RRB- have a long history of Christianity and Christian communities on its lands .
In ancient times , in the first centuries after the birth of Christ , when this region was called -LSB- by whom ? -RSB-
People of that time used to denote themselves Christians -LRB- христиане , крестьяне -RRB- and Russians -LRB- русские -RRB- .
Both terms had strong Christian connotations .
-LSB- citation needed -RSB- It is also interesting that in time the term '' крестьяне '' acquired the meaning `` peasants of Christian faith '' and later `` peasants '' -LRB- the main part of the population of the region -RRB- , while the term '' христиане '' retained its religious meaning and the term '' русские '' began to mean representatives of the heterogeneous Russian nation formed on the basis of common Christian faith and language , -LSB- citation needed -RSB- which strongly influenced the history and development of the region .
Also in some contexts the term `` cossack '' -LRB- козак , казак - free man by the will of God -RRB- was used -LSB- by whom ? -RSB-
to denote `` free '' Christians of steppe origin and Russian language .
As of the early 21st century , Christianity has approximately 2.4 billion adherents .
The faith represents about a third of the world 's population and is the largest religion in the world .
A 2011 Pew Research Center survey found that 76.2 % of Europeans , 73.3 % in Oceania , and about 86.0 % in the Americas -LRB- 90 % in Latin America and 77.4 % in North America -RRB- described themselves as Christians .
By 2050 , the Christian population is expected to exceed 3 billion .
While Muslims have an average of 3.1 children per woman -- the highest rate of all religious groups .
Christianity is growing in Africa , Asia , Latin America , Muslim world , and Oceania .
Overall , Protestants have won a total of 84.2 % of all the Nobel Prizes in Chemistry , 60 % in Medicine , and 58.6 % in Physics awarded to Americans between 1901 and 1972 .
Sony Music Entertainment Inc. -LRB- sometimes known as Sony Music or by the initials , SME -RRB- is an American music corporation managed and operated by Sony Corporation of America -LRB- SCA -RRB- , a subsidiary of Japanese conglomerate Sony Corporation .
The buyout led to the dissolution of BMG , which then relaunched as BMG Rights Management .
Out of the `` Big Three '' record companies , with Universal Music Group being the largest and Warner Music Group , SME is middle-sized .
The Columbia Phonograph Company had international subsidiaries and affiliates such as the Columbia Graphophone Company in the United Kingdom , but they were sold off prior to CBS acquiring American Columbia .
The renamed company made Columbia its flagship label with Okeh its subsidiary label while deemphasizing ARC 's other labels .
This allowed ARC 's leased labels Brunswick Records and Vocalion Records to revert to former owner Warner Bros. which sold the labels to Decca Records .
Columbia kept the Brunswick catalogue recorded from December 1931 onward which was reissued on the Columbia label as well as the Vocalion label material from the same time period which was reissued on the Okeh label .
Wallerstein , who was promoted at the end of 1947 from president to chairman of the record company , restored Columbia 's status as a leading record company and spearheaded the successful introduction of the long playing -LRB- LP -RRB- record before he retired as Columbia 's chairman in 1951 .
James Conkling then became head of Columbia Records .
Also in 1951 , Columbia severed its ties with the EMI-owned record label of the same name and began a UK distribution deal with Philips Records , whereas Okeh Records continued to be distributed by EMI on the Columbia label .
