One of the more prominent landmarks downtown is the Crystal Bridge at the Myriad Botanical Gardens , a large downtown urban park .
In 2007 , following a renovation of the stage , Oklahoma Shakespeare in the Park relocated to the Myriad Gardens .
The Myriad Gardens will undergo a massive renovation in conjunction with the recently built Devon Tower directly north of it .
The Oklahoma City Zoo and Botanical Garden is home to numerous natural habitats , WPA era architecture and landscaping , and hosts major touring concerts during the summer at its amphitheater .
Frontier City is an ` Old West ' - themed amusement park .
The park also features a recreation of a western gunfight at the ` OK Corral ' and many shops that line the `` Western '' town 's main street .
Frontier City also hosts a national concert circuit at its amphitheater during the summer .
Walking trails line Lake Hefner and Lake Overholser in the northwest part of the city and downtown at the canal and the Oklahoma River .
The majority of the east shore area is taken up by parks and trails , including a new leashless dog park and the postwar-era Stars and Stripes Park .
Oklahoma City has a major park in each quadrant of the city , going back to the first parks masterplan .
Martin Park Nature Center is a natural habitat in far northwest Oklahoma City .
Will Rogers Park is home to the Lycan Conservatory , the Rose Garden , and Butterfly Garden , all built in the WPA era .
Concerts and lectures are also held there .
The City of Oklahoma City has operated under a council-manager form of city government since 1927 .
Eight councilpersons represent each of the eight wards of Oklahoma City .
Couch previously served as assistant city manager , Metropolitan Area Projects Plan -LRB- MAPS -RRB- director and utilities director prior to his service as city manager .
The city is home to several colleges and universities .
OCU has its main campus in the north-central section of the city , near the city 's chinatown area .
OCU Law is located in the Midtown district near downtown , in the old Central High School building .
The OU Medicine hosting the state 's only Level-One trauma center .
OU is one of only four major universities in the nation to operate six medical schools .
