Universal subsequently severed its link to Mintz and formed its own in-house animation studio to produce Oswald cartoons headed by Walter Lantz .
He bought and built theaters , converted the studio to sound production , and made several forays into high-quality production .
Laemmle , Jr. created a niche for the studio , beginning a series of horror films which extended into the 1940s , affectionately dubbed Universal Horror .
Universal 's forays into high-quality production spelled the end of the Laemmle era at the studio .
Taking on the task of modernizing and upgrading a film conglomerate in the depths of the depression was risky , and for a time Universal slipped into receivership .
