The company reverted in name to Universal Pictures .
As a final gesture before leaving the talent agency business , virtually every MCA client was signed to a Universal contract .
And so , with MCA in charge , Universal became a full-blown , A-film movie studio , with leading actors and directors under contract ; offering slick , commercial films ; and a studio tour subsidiary launched in 1964 .
An innovation during this period championed by Universal was the made-for-television movie .
