The way that such church law is legislated , interpreted and at times adjudicated varies widely among these three bodies of churches .
There is a very early distinction between the rules enacted by the Church and the legislative measures taken by the State called leges , Latin for laws .
The actual subject material of the canons is not just doctrinal or moral in nature , but all-encompassing of the human condition .
Because of its specialized nature , advanced degrees in civil law or theology are normal prerequisites for the study of canon law .
The dogmatic decisions of the Councils , though , are to be obeyed rather than to be treated as guidelines , since they are essential for the Church 's unity .
