In 1659 Spain ceded Northern Catalonia to France , and Catalan was banned in both states in the early 18th century .
19th-century Spain saw a Catalan literary revival , which culminated in the 1913 orthographic standardization , and the officialization of the language during the Second Spanish Republic -LRB- 1931 -- 39 -RRB- .
However , the Francoist dictatorship -LRB- 1939 -- 75 -RRB- banned the language again .
Catalan dialects are relatively uniform , and are mutually intelligible .
These similarities are most notable with Occitan .
Pronouns are also inflected for case , animacy -LSB- citation needed -RSB- and politeness , and can be combined in very complex ways .
Verbs are split in several paradigms and are inflected for person , number , tense , aspect , mood , and gender .
The word Catalan derives from the territory of Catalonia , itself of disputed etymology .
Catalan can be pronounced as / ˈkætəlæn / , / kætəˈlæn / or / ˈkætələn / .
