All of these systems used interlacing and a 4:3 aspect ratio except the 240-line system which was progressive -LRB- actually described at the time by the technically correct term `` sequential '' -RRB- and the 405-line system which started as 5:4 and later changed to 4:3 .
The 240-line system could have doubled its frame rate but this would have meant that the transmitted signal would have doubled in bandwidth , an unacceptable option as the video baseband bandwidth was required to be not more than 3 MHz .
