In addition to skin color , other physical characteristics such as facial features and hair texture are often variously used in classifying peoples as black in South America and the Caribbean .
A Brazilian child was never automatically identified with the racial type of one or both of his or her parents , nor were there only two categories to choose from .
Scholars disagree over the effects of social status on racial classifications in Brazil .
In addition , people of mixed race -LRB- pardo -RRB- often tended to marry white , and their descendants became accepted as white .
