According to the last census of the 20th century , in which Brazilians could choose from five color/ethnic categories with which they identified , 54 % of individuals identified as white , 6.2 % identified as black , and 39.5 % identified as pardo -LRB- brown -RRB- -- a broad multi-racial category , including tri-racial persons .
Essentially most of the black population was absorbed into the multi-racial category by intermixing .
According to the 2010 census , 6.7 % of Brazilians said they were black , compared with 6.2 % in 2000 , and 43.1 % said they were racially mixed , up from 38.5 % .
The gap in income between blacks and other non-whites is relatively small compared to the large gap between whites and all people of color .
