These compositions used newly affordable electronic instruments to emulate not just Saunders ' song , but the edited , enhanced styles of disco and other dance music they already favored .
According to author Richie Unterberger , it moved house music away from its `` posthuman tendencies back towards the lush '' soulful sound of early disco music .
