By 1881 , the Central Mexican Railroad was completed which connected Mexico City to Ciudad Juárez .
By 1888 the telephone services were extended from the capital to the cites of Julimes , Meoqui , and Hidalgo del Parral ; the telecommunication network in the state covered an estimated 3,500 kilometers .
The need of laborers to construct the extensive infrastructure projects resulted in a significant Asian immigration , mostly from China .
By the end of the Terrazas term , the state experienced an increase in commerce , mining , and banking .
When the banks were nationalized , Chihuahua became the most important banking state in Mexico .
