The State of Bilaspur was merged in the Himachal Pradesh on 1 April 1954 by the Himachal Pradesh and Bilaspur -LRB- New State -RRB- Act , 1954 .
Himachal became a part C state on 26 January 1950 with the implementation of the Constitution of India and the Lt. Governor was appointed .
Legislative Assembly was elected in 1952 .
Following area of Punjab State namely Simla , Kangra , Kulu and Lahul and Spiti Districts , Nalagarh tehsil of Ambala District , Lohara , Amb and Una kanungo circles , some area of Santokhgarh kanungo circle and some other specified area of Una tehsil of Hoshiarpur District besides some parts of Dhar Kalan Kanungo circle of Pathankot tehsil of Gurdaspur District ; were merged with Himachal Pradesh on 1 November 1966 on enactment of Punjab Reorganisation Act , 1966 by the Parliament .
Thus Himachal emerged as the 18th state of the Indian Union .
