Efforts to deploy modern computers and networking equipment were generally successful , but attempts to develop new investigation software , outsourced to Science Applications International Corporation -LRB- SAIC -RRB- , were not .
Virtual Case File , or VCF , as the software was known , was plagued by poorly defined goals , and repeated changes in management .
At least $ 100 million -LRB- and much more by some estimates -RRB- was spent on the project , which never became operational .
The FBI has been forced to continue using its decade-old Automated Case Support system , which IT experts consider woefully inadequate .
In March 2005 , the FBI announced it was beginning a new , more ambitious software project , code-named Sentinel , which they expected to complete by 2009 .
