Because of these three ancient Vyākaraṇins -LRB- grammarians -RRB- , this grammar is called Trimuni Vyākarana .
To understand the meaning of the sutras , Jayaditya and Vāmana wrote a commentary , the Kāsikā , in 600 CE .
Pāṇinian grammar is based on 14 Shiva sutras -LRB- aphorisms -RRB- , where the whole mātrika -LRB- alphabet -RRB- is abbreviated .
Though they are quite similar , they differ in a number of essential points of phonology , vocabulary , grammar and syntax .
