A blockade of Wilhelmshaven failed and conflicting orders about operations in the Baltic Sea or a return to France , made the French naval efforts futile .
The French General Staff -- along with those of every other European military -- was little better than a collection of assistants for the line commanders .
This disorganization hampered the French commanders ' ability to exercise control of their forces .
