Eritrea -LRB- / ˌɛrᵻˈtreɪ.ə / or / ˌɛrᵻˈtriːə / ; , officially the State of Eritrea , is a country in East Africa .
Its name Eritrea is based on the Greek name for the Red Sea -LRB- Ἐρυθρὰ Θάλασσα Erythra Thalassa -RRB- , which was first adopted for Italian Eritrea in 1890 .
