The name Eritrea is derived from the ancient Greek name for Red Sea -LRB- Ἐρυθρὰ Θάλασσα Erythra Thalassa , based on the adjective ἐρυθρός erythros `` red '' -RRB- .
It was first formally adopted in 1890 , with the formation of Italian Eritrea -LRB- Colonia Eritrea -RRB- .
The territory became the Eritrea Governorate within Italian East Africa in 1936 .
