Honorary appointees who later become a citizen of a Commonwealth realm can convert their appointment from honorary to substantive , then enjoy all privileges of membership of the order including use of the title of Sir and Dame for the senior two ranks of the Order .
In many of these systems , the different levels of award and honour reflect the Imperial system they replaced .
