For its complete North American release , the Nintendo Entertainment System was progressively released over the ensuing years in four different bundles : the Deluxe Set , the Control Deck , the Action Set and the Power Set .
In 1989 , the Power Set included the console , two game controllers , a NES Zapper , a Power Pad , and a triple Game Pak containing Super Mario Bros , Duck Hunt , and World Class Track Meet .
In 1990 , a Sports Set bundle was released , including the console , an NES Satellite infrared wireless multitap adapter , four game controllers , and a dual Game Pak containing Super Spike V'Ball and Nintendo World Cup .
Two more bundle packages were later released using the original model NES console .
The Challenge Set of 1992 included the console , two controllers , and a Super Mario Bros. 3 Game Pak for a retail price of US$ 89.99 .
It included only the console and two controllers , and no longer was bundled with a cartridge .
Instead , it contained a book called the Official Nintendo Player 's Guide , which contained detailed information for every NES game made up to that point .
Others have been produced with certain specialized markets in mind , such as an NES clone that functions as a rather primitive personal computer , which includes a keyboard and basic word processing software .
