In about 319 , when Athanasius was a deacon , a presbyter named Arius came into a direct conflict with Alexander of Alexandria .
It appears that Arius reproached Alexander for what he felt were misguided or heretical teachings being taught by the bishop .
Arius 's theological views appear to have been firmly rooted in Alexandrian Christianity , and his Christological views were certainly not radical at all .
That council also denounced various heresies and schisms , many of which continued to preoccupy his 45-year-long episcopate -LRB- c. 8 June 328 -- 2 May 373 -RRB- .
This gave rise to the expression `` Athanasius contra mundum '' or `` Athanasius against the world '' .
