By 1910 , Seattle was one of the 25 largest cities in the country .
However , the Great Depression severely damaged the city 's economy .
In 1994 the Internet retail giant Amazon was founded in Seattle .
The stream of new software , biotechnology , and Internet companies led to an economic revival , which increased the city 's population by almost 50,000 between 1990 and 2000 .
The Seattle metropolitan area of around 3.6 million inhabitants is the 15th largest metropolitan area in the United States .
In 1855 , nominal land settlements were established .
