A 1912 city development plan by Virgil Bogue went largely unused .
Seattle was mildly prosperous in the 1920s but was particularly hard hit in the Great Depression , experiencing some of the country 's harshest labor strife in that era .
In 1993 , the movie Sleepless in Seattle brought the city further national attention .
Lake Washington 's waters flow to Puget Sound through the Lake Washington Ship Canal -LRB- consisting of two man-made canals , Lake Union , and the Hiram M. Chittenden Locks at Salmon Bay , ending in Shilshole Bay on Puget Sound -RRB- .
Yet another boom began as the city emerged from the Great Recession .
Other strong quakes occurred on January 26 , 1700 -LRB- estimated at 9 magnitude -RRB- , December 14 , 1872 -LRB- 7.3 or 7.4 -RRB- , April 13 , 1949 -LRB- 7.1 -RRB- , and April 29 , 1965 -LRB- 6.5 -RRB- .
The 1965 quake caused three deaths in Seattle directly , and one more by heart failure .
Although the Seattle Fault passes just south of the city center , neither it nor the Cascadia subduction zone has caused an earthquake since the city 's founding .
The city itself is hilly , though not uniformly so .
The Wallingford , Mount Baker , and Crown Hill neighborhoods are technically located on hills as well .
The break in the ridge between First Hill and Beacon Hill is man-made , the result of two of the many regrading projects that reshaped the topography of the city center .
Annual precipitation has ranged from 23.78 in -LRB- 604 mm -RRB- in 1952 to 55.14 in -LRB- 1,401 mm -RRB- in 1950 ; for water year -LRB- October 1 -- September 30 -RRB- precipitation , the range is 23.16 in -LRB- 588 mm -RRB- in 1976 -- 77 to 51.82 in -LRB- 1,316 mm -RRB- in 1996 -- 97 .
The city of Bremerton , about 15 mi -LRB- 24 km -RRB- west of downtown Seattle , receives 56.4 in -LRB- 1,430 mm -RRB- of precipitation annually .
By comparison , Fort Myers , Florida reports thunder on 93 days per year , Kansas City on 52 , and New York City on 25 .
Despite being on the margin of the rain shadow of the Olympic Mountains , the city has a reputation for frequent rain .
In an average year , at least 0.01 inches -LRB- 0.25 mm -RRB- of precipitation falls on 150 days , more than nearly all U.S. cities east of the Rocky Mountains .
It is cloudy 201 days out of the year and partly cloudy 93 days .
In the convergence zone , air arriving from the north meets air flowing in from the south .
When the air currents meet , they are forced upward , resulting in convection .
Thunderstorms caused by this activity are usually weak and can occur north and south of town , but Seattle itself rarely receives more than occasional thunder and small hail showers .
This moderate snow event was officially the 12th snowiest calendar day at the airport since 1948 and snowiest since November 1985 .
Much of the city of Seattle proper received somewhat lesser snowfall accumulations .
Locations to the south of Seattle received more , with Olympia and Chehalis receiving 14 to 18 in -LRB- 36 to 46 cm -RRB- .
From January 31 to February 2 , 1916 , another heavy snow event occurred with 29 in -LRB- 74 cm -RRB- of snow on the ground by the time the event was over .
With official records dating to 1948 , the largest single-day snowfall is 20.0 in -LRB- 51 cm -RRB- on January 13 , 1950 .
Seasonal snowfall has ranged from zero in 1991 -- 92 to 67.5 in -LRB- 171 cm -RRB- in 1968 -- 69 , with trace amounts having occurred as recently as 2009 -- 10 .
The month of January 1950 was particularly severe , bringing 57.2 in -LRB- 145 cm -RRB- of snow , the most of any month along with the aforementioned record cold .
Autumn , winter , and early spring are frequently characterized by rain .
The hottest officially recorded temperature was 103 °F -LRB- 39 °C -RRB- on July 29 , 2009 ; the coldest recorded temperature was 0 °F -LRB- − 18 °C -RRB- on January 31 , 1950 ; the record cold daily maximum is 16 °F -LRB- − 9 °C -RRB- on January 14 , 1950 , while , conversely , the record warm daily minimum is 71 °F -LRB- 22 °C -RRB- the day the official record high was set .
Light rain & drizzle are the predominant forms of precipitation during the remainder of the year ; for instance , on average , less than 1.6 in -LRB- 41 mm -RRB- of rain falls in July and August combined when rain is rare .
On occasion , Seattle experiences somewhat more significant weather events .
Precipitation totals exceeded 13.8 in -LRB- 350 mm -RRB- in some areas with winds topping out at 209 km/h -LRB- 130 mph -RRB- along coastal Oregon .
It became the second wettest event in Seattle history when a little over 130 mm -LRB- 5.1 in -RRB- of rain fell on Seattle in a 24-hour period .
In recent years , the city has experienced steady population growth , and has been faced with the issue of accommodating more residents .
The Chinese population in the Seattle area has origins in mainland China , Hong Kong , Southeast Asia , and Taiwan .
According to a 2012 HistoryLink study , Seattle 's 98118 ZIP code -LRB- in the Columbia City neighborhood -RRB- was one of the most diverse ZIP Code Tabulation Areas in the United States .
The 2010 census showed that Seattle was one of the whitest big cities in the country , although its proportion of white residents has been gradually declining .
Still , very large companies dominate the business landscape .
Other Fortune 500 companies popularly associated with Seattle are based in nearby Puget Sound cities .
