Ali and his supporters were stunned by the decision which had lowered the Caliph to the status of the rebellious Muawiyah I. Ali was therefore outwitted by Muawiyah and Amr .
Ali refused to accept the verdict and found himself technically in breach of his pledge to abide by the arbitration .
This put Ali in a weak position even amongst his own supporters .
The most vociferous opponents in Ali 's camp were the very same people who had forced Ali into the ceasefire .
