On 4 April , led by Ney , they confronted Napoleon .
Napoleon asserted the army would follow him , and Ney replied the army would follow its generals .
While the ordinary soldiers and regimental officers wanted to fight on , without any senior officers or marshals any prospective invasion of Paris would have been impossible .
Bowing to the inevitable , on 4 April Napoleon abdicated in favour of his son , with Marie-Louise as regent .
However , the Allies refused to accept this under prodding from Alexander , who feared that Napoleon might find an excuse to retake the throne .
Napoleon was then forced to announce his unconditional abdication only two days later .
Napoleon attempted suicide with a pill he had carried after nearly being captured by the Russians during the retreat from Moscow .
