Dark meat , which avian myologists refer to as `` red muscle '' , is used for sustained activity -- chiefly walking , in the case of a chicken .
Thus , the chicken 's leg and thigh meat are dark , while its breast meat -LRB- which makes up the primary flight muscles -RRB- is white .
