Visible light is measured in lumens , a unit which is defined in part by the differing sensitivity of the human eye to different wavelengths of light .
Not all wavelengths of visible electromagnetic energy are equally effective at stimulating the human eye ; the luminous efficacy of radiant energy -LRB- LER -RRB- is a measure of how well the distribution of energy matches the perception of the eye .
The units of luminous efficacy are `` lumens per watt '' -LRB- lpw -RRB- .
Even at this high temperature , a lot of the radiation is either infrared or ultraviolet , and the theoretical luminous efficacy -LRB- LER -RRB- is 95 lumens per watt . ''
