In April 1950 , Stalin gave Kim permission to invade the South under the condition that Mao would agree to send reinforcements if they became needed .
Kim met with Mao in May 1950 .
At that time , the Chinese were in the process of demobilizing half of the PLA 's 5.6 million soldiers .
However , Mao sent more ethnic Korean PLA veterans to Korea and promised to move an army closer to the Korean border .
