Greece is strategically located at the crossroads of Europe , Asia , and Africa .
The Aegean Sea lies to the east of the mainland , the Ionian Sea to the west , and the Mediterranean Sea to the south .
Greece has one of the longest histories of any country , and is considered the cradle of Western civilization , and as such , is the birthplace of democracy , Western philosophy , the Olympic Games , Western literature , historiography , political science , major scientific and mathematical principles , and Western drama , including both tragedy and comedy .
Greece 's rich historical legacy is reflected in large part by its 17 UNESCO World Heritage Sites , among the most in Europe and the world .
It is also a member of numerous other international institutions , including the Council of Europe , NATO , -LSB- a -RSB- OECD , OIF , OSCE and the WTO .
The names for the nation of Greece and the Greek people differ from the names used in other languages , locations and cultures .
However , the name Hellas is sometimes used in English as well .
These civilizations possessed writing , the Minoans writing in an undeciphered script known as Linear A , and the Mycenaeans in Linear B , an early form of Greek .
These states and their colonies reached great levels of prosperity that resulted in an unprecedented cultural boom , that of classical Greece , expressed in architecture , drama , science , mathematics and philosophy .
A second invasion by the Persians followed in 480 BC .
Following decisive Greek victories in 480 and 479 BC at Salamis , Plataea , and Mycale , the Persians were forced to withdraw for a second time , marking their eventual withdrawal from all of their European territories .
Similarly , most Roman emperors maintained an admiration for things Greek in nature .
Hadrian was also particularly fond of the Greeks ; before he became emperor he served as an eponymous archon of Athens .
Greek-speaking communities of the Hellenized East were instrumental in the spread of early Christianity in the 2nd and 3rd centuries , and Christianity 's early leaders and writers -LRB- notably St Paul -RRB- were mostly Greek-speaking , though generally not from Greece itself .
In Athens and rural areas , paganism is attested well into the sixth century AD and even later .
Some remote areas such as the southeastern Peloponnese remained pagan until well into the 10th century AD .
Outside of these areas , a limited amount of Slavic settlement is generally thought to have occurred , although on a much smaller scale than previously thought .
