The highest Protestant concentrations are in the small villages of southern and western Thuringia , whereas the bigger cities are even more non-religious -LRB- up to 88 % in Gera -RRB- .
Catholic regions are the Eichsfeld in the northwest and parts of the Rhön Mountains around Geisa in the southwest .
Protestant church membership is shrinking rapidly , whereas the Catholic Church is somewhat more stable because of Catholic migration from Poland , Southern Europe and West Germany .
Other religions play no significant role in Thuringia .
Furthermore , there are some Orthodox communities of Eastern European migrants and some traditional Protestant Free churches in Thuringia without any societal influence .
Their origin is not completely known .
An older theory claimed that they were successors of the Hermunduri , but later research rejected the idea .
Their various lands formed the Free State of Thuringia , founded in 1920 , together with some other small principalities .
With the division of the house of Wettin in 1485 , Thuringia went to the senior Ernestine branch of the family , which subsequently subdivided the area into a number of smaller states , according to the Saxon tradition of dividing inheritance amongst male heirs .
In Mühlhausen and elsewhere , the Anabaptists found many adherents .
In 1920 , after World War I , these small states merged into one state , called Thuringia ; only Saxe-Coburg voted to join Bavaria instead .
The coat of arms of this new state was simpler than they had been previously .
He also ensured that whenever an important position came up within Thuringia , he used his power to ensure that a Nazi was given that post .
The landscapes of Thuringia are quite diverse .
The central and northern part of Thuringia is defined by the 3000 km ² wide Thuringian Basin , a very fertile and flat area around the Unstrut river and completely surrounded by the following hill chains -LRB- clockwise from the north-west -RRB- : Dün , Hainleite , Windleite , Kyffhäuser , Hohe Schrecke , Schmücke , Finne , Ettersberg , Steigerwald , Thuringian Forest , Hörselberge and Hainich .
Within the Basin the smaller hill chains Fahner Höhe and Heilinger Höhen .
South of the Thuringian Basin is the Land 's largest mountain range , marked by the Thuringian Forest in the north-west , the Thuringian Highland in the middle and the Franconian Forest in the south-east .
To the south-west , the Forest is followed up by Werra river valley , dividing it from the Rhön Mountains in the west and the Grabfeld plain in the south .
Eastern Thuringia , commonly described as the area east of Saale and Loquitz valley , is marked by a hilly landscape , rising slowly from the flat north to the mountainous south .
The far eastern region -LRB- east of Weiße Elster -RRB- is the Osterland or Altenburger Land along Pleiße river , a flat , fertile and densely settled agricultural area .
Thuringia is Germany 's only state without connection to navigable waterways .
However , most of the plains have been cleared and are in intensive agricultural use while most of the forests are planted with spruce and pine .
In comparison to the forest , agriculture is still quite conventional and dominated by large structures and monocultures .
Since the beginning of Urbanisation around 1840 , the Thuringian cities have higher growth rates resp .
Migration plays an important role in Thuringia .
The internal migration shows a strong tendency from rural areas towards the big cities .
Between Thuringia and the other German states , the balance is negative : In 2012 , Thuringia lost 6,500 persons to other federal states , the most to Bavaria , Saxony , Hesse and Berlin .
Only with Saxony-Anhalt and Brandenburg the balance is positive .
In 2009 , the balance was +700 , in 2010 +1,800 , in 2011 +2,700 and in 2012 +4,800 .
The most important countries of origin of the Thuringia migrants from 2008 to 2012 were Poland -LRB- +1,700 -RRB- , Romania -LRB- +1,200 -RRB- , Afghanistan -LRB- +1,100 -RRB- and Serbia/Montenegro/Kosovo -LRB- +1,000 -RRB- , whereas the balance was negative with Switzerland -LRB- − 2,800 -RRB- and Austria -LRB- − 900 -RRB- .
Today , all municipalities within districts are equal in law , whether they are towns or villages .
The most important industrial branches today are engineering and metalworking , vehicle production and food industries .
On the other hand , the late 19th century brought new types of mines to Thuringia : the lignite surface mining around Meuselwitz near Altenburg in the east of the Land started in the 1870s , and two potash mining districts were established around 1900 .
Together , they accounted for a significant part of the world 's potash production in the mid-20th century .
The centre was Ronneburg near Gera in eastern Thuringia and the operating company Wismut was under direct Soviet control .
The decrease is caused on the one hand by the emergence of new jobs and on the other by a marked decrease in the working-age population , caused by emigration and low birth rates for decades .
External immigration into Thuringia has been encouraged by the government since about 2010 to counter this problem .
The A4 runs from Frankfurt in Hesse via Eisenach , Gotha , Erfurt , Weimar , Jena and Gera to Dresden in Saxony , connecting Thuringia 's most important cities .
At Hermsdorf junction it is connected with the A9 .
The A71 crosses the Land in southwest-northeast direction , connecting Würzburg in Bavaria via Meiningen , Suhl , Ilmenau , Arnstadt , Erfurt and Sömmerda with Sangerhausen and Halle in Saxony-Anhalt .
The A73 starts at the A71 south of Erfurt in Suhl and runs south towards Nuremberg in Bavaria .
The A38 is another west-east connection in the north of Thuringia running from Göttingen in Lower Saxony via Heiligenstadt and Nordhausen to Leipzig in Saxony .
Furthermore , there is a dense network of federal highways complementing the motorway network .
Envisaged projects include upgrades of the B247 from Gotha to Leinefelde to improve Mühlhausen 's connection to the national road network , the B19 from Eisenach to Meiningen to improve access to Bad Salzungen and Schmalkalden , and the B88 and B281 for strengthening the Saalfeld/Rudolstadt region .
Health care in Thuringia is currently undergoing a concentration process .
Early-years education is quite common in Thuringia .
The German higher education system comprises two forms of academic institutions : universities and polytechnics -LRB- Fachhochschule -RRB- .
It was founded in 1558 , and today has 21,000 students .
The second-largest is the Technische Universität Ilmenau with 7,000 students , founded in 1894 , which offers many technical disciplines such as engineering and mathematics .
Finally , there are colleges for those studying for a technical qualification while working in a related field -LRB- Berufsakademie -RRB- at Eisenach -LRB- 600 students -RRB- and Gera -LRB- 700 students -RRB- .
Thuringia 's leading research centre is Jena , followed by Ilmenau .
By 1920 , many branch lines had been built , giving Thuringia one of the densest rail networks in the world before World War II with about 2,500 km of track .
On the other hand , most of the main lines were refurbished after 1990 , resulting in improved speed of travel .
The most important railway lines at present are the Thuringian Railway , connecting Halle and Leipzig via Weimar , Erfurt , Gotha and Eisenach with Frankfurt and Kassel and the Saal Railway from Halle/Leipzig via Jena and Saalfeld to Nuremberg .
The former has an hourly ICE/IC service from Dresden to Frankfurt while the latter is served hourly by ICE trains from Berlin to Munich .
Both ICE routes will then use the Erfurt -- Leipzig/Halle high-speed railway , and the Berlin-Munich route will continue via the Nuremberg -- Erfurt high-speed railway .
Only the segment west of Erfurt of the Frankfurt-Dresden line will continue to be used by ICE trains after 2017 , with an increased line speed of 200 km/h -LRB- currently 160 km/h -RRB- .
Erfurt 's central station , which was completely rebuilt for this purpose in the 2000s -LRB- decade -RRB- , will be the new connection between both ICE lines .
The most important regional railway lines in Thuringia are the Neudietendorf -- Ritschenhausen railway from Erfurt to Würzburg and Meiningen , the Weimar -- Gera railway from Erfurt to Chemnitz , the Sangerhausen -- Erfurt railway from Erfurt to Magdeburg , the Gotha -- Leinefelde railway from Erfurt to Göttingen , the Halle -- Kassel railway from Halle via Nordhausen to Kassel and the Leipzig -- Hof railway from Leipzig via Altenburg to Zwickau and Hof .
Most regional and local lines have hourly service , but some run only every other hour .
Thus predation is often , though not always , carnivory .
All these consumption categories fall under the rubric of consumer-resource systems .
It can often be difficult to separate various types of feeding behaviors .
Some predators kill large prey and dismember or chew it prior to eating it , such as a jaguar or a human ; others may eat their -LRB- usually much smaller -RRB- prey whole , as does a bottlenose dolphin swallowing a fish , or a snake , duck or stork swallowing a frog .
In some cases , the venom , as in rattlesnakes and some spiders , contributes to the digestion of the prey item even before the predator begins eating .
In other cases , the prey organism may die in the mouth or digestive system of the predator .
Seed predation and egg predation are other forms of true predation , as seeds and eggs represent potential organisms .
Predators of this classification need not eat prey entirely .
For example , some predators can not digest bones , while others can .
Some may eat only part of an organism , as in grazing -LRB- see below -RRB- , but still consistently cause its direct death .
Grazing livestock may pull some grass out at the roots , but most is simply grazed upon , allowing the plant to regrow once again .
Some species however have more loose associations with their hosts .
Lepidoptera -LRB- butterfly and moth -RRB- larvae may feed parasitically on only a single plant , or they may graze on several nearby plants .
They are much like parasites in their close symbiotic relationship with their host or hosts .
Like the previous two classifications parasitoid predators do not kill their hosts instantly .
However , unlike parasites , they are very similar to true predators in that the fate of their prey is quite inevitably death .
By this stage the young wasp -LRB- s -RRB- are developed sufficiently to move to the next stage in their life cycle .
Among predators there is a large degree of specialization .
Many predators specialize in hunting only one species of prey .
The specialists are usually particularly well suited to capturing their preferred prey .
The prey in turn , are often equally suited to escape that predator .
Some predators specialize in certain classes of prey , not just single species .
-LSB- citation needed -RSB-
Predators are often another organism 's prey , and likewise prey are often predators .
Though blue jays prey on insects , they may in turn be prey for cats and snakes , and snakes may be the prey of hawks .
Secondary consumers are a type of carnivore , but there are also tertiary consumers eating these carnivores , quartary consumers eating them , and so forth .
A carnivore may eat both secondary and tertiary consumers , and its prey may itself be difficult to classify for similar reasons .
Even herbivores such as the giant panda may supplement their diet with meat .
Another manner in which predation and competition are connected is throughout intraguild predation .
For example , grazers of a grassland may prevent a single dominant species from taking over .
The relationship between predator and prey is one that is typically beneficial to the predator , and detrimental to the prey species .
The more convincing camouflage is , the more likely it is that the organism will go unseen .
Another example of batesian mimicry is the io moth , -LRB- Automeris io -RRB- , which has markings on its wings that resemble an owl 's eyes .
Female fireflies of the genus Photuris , for example , copy the light signals of other species , thereby attracting male fireflies , which are then captured and eaten -LRB- see aggressive mimicry -RRB- .
When hunger is not an issue , in general most predators will not seek to attack prey since the costs outweigh the benefits .
For instance , a large predatory fish like a shark that is well fed in an aquarium will typically ignore the smaller fish swimming around it -LRB- while the prey fish take advantage of the fact that the apex predator is apparently uninterested -RRB- .
Surplus killing represents a deviation from this type of behaviour .
Social predation allows some animals to organize hunts of creatures that would easily escape a single predator ; thus chimpanzees can prey upon colobus monkeys , and Harris 's hawks can cut off all possible escapes for a doomed rabbit .
Even without complex intelligence but instinct alone , some ant species can destroy much larger creatures .
Pet cats and pet mice , for example , may live together in the same human residence without incident as companions .
Predatory animals often use their usual methods of attacking prey to inflict or to threaten grievous injury to their own predators .
Mobbing can be an interspecies activity : it is common for birds to respond to mobbing calls of a different species .
Many birds will show up at the sight of mobbing and watch and call , but not participate .
Some organisms pose a threat to their predators -- for example they may be poisonous , or able to harm them physically .
For example , bright coloration in Variable Checkerspot butterflies leads to decreased predation attempts by avian predators .
It is obvious that predators depend on prey for survival , and this is reflected in predator populations being affected by changes in prey populations .
It is not so obvious , however , that predators affect prey populations .
Humans also lack innate weaponry such as claws .
Without crafted weapons , society , or cleverness , a lone human can easily be defeated by fit predatory animals , such as wild dogs , big cats and bears -LRB- see Man-eater -RRB- .
However , humans are not solitary creatures ; they are social animals with highly developed social behaviors .
Cannibalism has occurred in various places , among various cultures , and for various reasons .
Low numbers would n't be a problem for apex predators if there was an abundance of prey and no competition or niche overlap , a scenario that is rarely , if ever , encountered in the wild .
A predator 's effect on its prey species is hard to see in the short-term .
If a predator overhunts its prey , the prey population will lower to numbers that are too scarce for the predators to find .
This will cause the predator population to dip , decreasing the predation pressure on the prey population .
The decrease in predators will allow the small number of prey left to slowly increase their population to somewhere around their previous abundance , which will allow the predator population to increase in response to the greater availability of resources .
This is a risk that wildlife conservationists encounter when introducing predators to prey that have not coevolved with the same or similar predators .
This possibility depends largely on how well and how fast the prey species is able to adapt to the introduced predator .
One way that this risk can be avoided is if the predator finds an alternative prey species or if an alternative prey species is introduced -LRB- something that ecologists and environmentalists try to avoid whenever possible -RRB- .
An alternative prey species would help to lift some of the predation pressure from the initial prey species , giving the population a chance to recover , however it does not guarantee that the initial prey species will be able to recover as the initial prey population may have been hunted to below sustainable numbers or to complete extinction .
Predators may be put to use in conservation efforts to control introduced species .
Predators from its natural range may be introduced to control populations , though in some cases this has little effect , and may even cause unforeseen problems .
