As of July 2013 , about 100 political prisoners remain imprisoned , while conflict between the Burmese Army and local insurgent groups continues .
It is bounded by Laos and Thailand to the southeast .
Smaller mammals are also numerous , ranging from gibbons and monkeys to flying foxes and tapirs .
