The government of Myanmar controls the gem trade by direct ownership or by joint ventures with private owners of mines .
They are not to discuss politics with foreigners , under penalty of imprisonment and , in 2001 , the Myanmar Tourism Promotion Board issued an order for local officials to protect tourists and limit `` unnecessary contact '' between foreigners and ordinary Burmese people .
There are a small number of border crossings that allow the passage of private vehicles , such as the border between Ruili -LRB- China -RRB- to Mu-se , the border between Htee Kee -LRB- Myanmar -RRB- and Ban Phu Nam Ron -LRB- Thailand -RRB- -LRB- the most direct border between Dawei and Kanchanaburi -RRB- , and the border between Myawaddy -LRB- Myanmar -RRB- and Mae Sot -LRB- Thailand -RRB- .
