Population density is 76 per square kilometre -LRB- 200/sq mi -RRB- , among the lowest in Southeast Asia .
10 % of the population are Shan .
The Kayin make up 7 % of the population .
Overseas Indians are 2 % .
The remainder are Kachin , Chin , Rohingya , Anglo-Indians , Gurkha , Nepali and other ethnic minorities .
It is estimated that 52,000 Anglo-Burmese remain in Myanmar .
As of 2009 -LSB- update -RSB- , 110,000 Burmese refugees were living in refugee camps in Thailand .
Sino-Tibetan languages are most widely spoken .
They include Burmese , Karen , Kachin , Chin , and Chinese -LRB- mainly Hokkien -RRB- .
Mon , Palaung , and Wa are the major Austroasiatic languages spoken in Myanmar .
It is also used to write Pali , the sacred language of Theravada Buddhism , as well as several ethnic minority languages , including Shan , several Karen dialects , and Kayah -LRB- Karenni -RRB- , with the addition of specialised characters and diacritics for each language .
Religious edifices and orders have been in existence for many years .
Such persecution and targeting of civilians is particularly notable in Eastern Myanmar , where over 3000 villages have been destroyed in the past ten years .
More than 200,000 Muslims have fled to Bangladesh over the last 20 years to escape Islamophobic persecution .
Independent researchers put the Muslim population at 6 to 10 % of the population -LSB- citation needed -RSB- .
This is manifested in its language , cuisine , music , dance and theatre .
Considered the national epic of Myanmar , the Yama Zatdaw , an adaptation of India 's Ramayana , has been influenced greatly by Thai , Mon , and Indian versions of the play .
Monks are venerated and supported by the lay people .
All male children in Buddhist families are encouraged to be a novice -LRB- beginner for Buddhism -RRB- before the age of twenty and to be a monk after the age of twenty .
British colonial rule introduced Western elements of culture to Burma .
Burma 's education system is modelled after that of the United Kingdom .
Many ethnic minorities , particularly the Karen in the southeast and the Kachin and Chin who populate the north and northeast , practice Christianity .
During the 1920s and 1930s , many Burmese-owned film companies made and produced several films .
The first Burmese sound film was produced in 1932 in Bombay , India with the title Ngwe Pay Lo Ma Ya -LRB- Money Ca n't Buy It -RRB- .
Though few sources in the Bible mention the exilic periods in detail , the experience of diaspora life , from the Ancient Egyptian rule over the Levant , to Assyrian Captivity and Exile , to Babylonian Captivity and Exile , to Seleucid Imperial rule , to the Roman occupation , and the historical relations between Israelites and the homeland , became a major feature of Jewish history , identity and memory .
These numbers include all those who self-identified as Jews in a socio-demographic study or were identified as such by a respondent in the same household .
The exact world Jewish population , however , is difficult to measure .
