It has a 109,901 seating capacity after multiple renovations were made .
Crisler Center and Yost Ice Arena play host to the school 's basketball -LRB- both men 's and women 's -RRB- and ice hockey teams , respectively .
Concordia University , a member of the NAIA , also fields sports teams .
The city itself is often called `` A ² '' -LRB- `` A-squared '' -RRB- or `` A2 '' -LRB- `` A two '' -RRB- or `` AA '' , `` The Deuce '' -LRB- mainly by Chicagoans -RRB- , and `` Tree Town '' .
In A Prairie Home Companion broadcast from Ann Arbor , Garrison Keillor described Ann Arbor as `` a city where people discuss socialism , but only in the fanciest restaurants . ''
Ann Arbor sometimes appears on citation indexes as an author , instead of a location , often with the academic degree MI , a misunderstanding of the abbreviation for Michigan .
The mayor is elected citywide .
The mayor is the presiding officer of the City Council and has the power to appoint all Council committee members as well as board and commission members , with the approval of the City Council .
The current mayor of Ann Arbor is Christopher Taylor , a Democrat who was elected as mayor in 2014 .
Day-to-day city operations are managed by a city administrator chosen by the city council .
In the Michigan House of Representatives , representation is split between the 55th district -LRB- northern Ann Arbor , part of Ann Arbor Township , and other surrounding areas , represented by Democrat Adam Zemke -RRB- , the 53rd district -LRB- most of downtown and the southern half of the city , represented by Democrat Jeff Irwin -RRB- and the 52nd district -LRB- southwestern areas outside Ann Arbor proper and western Washtenaw County , represented by Democrat Gretchen Driskell -RRB- .
In 1974 , Kathy Kozachenko 's victory in an Ann Arbor city-council race made her the country 's first openly homosexual candidate to win public office .
Adopted through a ballot initiative sponsored by the local Human Rights Party , which feared a splintering of the liberal vote , the process was repealed in 1976 after use in only one election .
As of August 2009 , Democrats hold the mayorship and all council seats .
The left tilt of politics in the city has earned it the nickname `` The People 's Republic of Ann Arbor '' .
Nationally , Ann Arbor is located in Michigan 's 12th congressional district , represented by Democrat Debbie Dingell .
Washtenaw Community College is located in neighboring Ann Arbor Township .
Public schools are part of the Ann Arbor Public Schools -LRB- AAPS -RRB- district .
There were 21 elementary schools , five middle schools -LRB- Forsythe , Slauson , Tappan , Scarlett , and Clague -RRB- three traditional high schools -LRB- Pioneer , Huron , and Skyline -RRB- , and three alternative high schools -LRB- Community High , Stone School , and Roberto Clemente -RRB- in the district .
This program is open to all families who live within the district .
Ann Arbor Public Schools also operates a preschool and family center , with programs for at-risk infants and children before kindergarten .
The district has a preschool center with both free and tuition-based programs for preschoolers in the district .
