As Secretary of State Montini coordinated the activities of assistance to the persecuted hidden in convents , parishes , seminaries , and in ecclesiastical schools .
In Rome alone this organization distributed almost two million portions of free food in the year 1944 .
After the war and later as pope , Montini turned the Pontificia Commissione di Assistenza , into the major charity , Caritas Italiana .
