More recently Vladimir Prelog , Heinrich Rohrer , Richard Ernst , Edmond Fischer , Rolf Zinkernagel and Kurt Wüthrich received Nobel prizes in the sciences .
Another important research center is the Paul Scherrer Institute .
The western French-speaking areas and the urban regions of the rest of the country tend to be more pro-EU , however with far from any significant share of the population .
The government has established an Integration Office under the Department of Foreign Affairs and the Department of Economic Affairs .
These agreements were signed in 1999 and took effect in 2001 .
They continue to discuss further areas for cooperation .
A further referendum will be needed to approve 300 million francs to support Romania and Bulgaria and their recent admission .
Preparatory discussions are being opened in four new areas : opening up the electricity market , participation in the European GNSS project Galileo , cooperating with the European centre for disease prevention and recognising certificates of origin for food products .
`` Fukushima showed that the risk of nuclear power is too high , which in turn has also increased the costs of this energy form . ''
Parliament will discuss the plan in June 2011 , and there could be a referendum as well .
The Swiss autobahn/autoroute network has a total length of 1,638 km -LRB- 1,018 mi -RRB- -LRB- as of 2000 -RRB- and has , by an area of 41,290 km2 -LRB- 15,940 sq mi -RRB- , also one of the highest motorway densities in the world .
The other international airports are Geneva Airport -LRB- 13.9 million passengers in 2012 -RRB- , EuroAirport Basel-Mulhouse-Freiburg which is located in France , Bern Airport , Lugano Airport , St. Gallen-Altenrhein Airport and Sion Airport .
Its main hub is Zürich .
In many places in Switzerland , household rubbish disposal is charged for .
Illegal disposal of garbage is not tolerated but usually the enforcement of such laws is limited to violations that involve the unlawful disposal of larger volumes at traffic intersections and public areas .
