However , federal laws and other official acts do not need to be decreed in Romansh .
German Helvetisms are , roughly speaking , a large group of words typical of Swiss Standard German , which do not appear either in Standard German , nor in other German dialects .
These include terms from Switzerland 's surrounding language cultures -LRB- German Billette from French -RRB- , from similar term in another language -LRB- Italian azione used not only as act but also as discount from German Aktion -RRB- .
The French spoken in Switzerland has similar terms , which are equally known as Helvetisms .
Duden , one of the prescriptive sources for Standard German , is aware of about 3000 Helvetisms .
While the cost of the system is among the highest it compares well with other European countries in terms of health outcomes ; patients who are citizens have been reported as being , in general , highly satisfied with it .
