Protein molecules contain nitrogen atoms in addition to carbon , oxygen , and hydrogen .
Some of the amino acids are convertible -LRB- with the expenditure of energy -RRB- to glucose and can be used for energy production , just as ordinary glucose , in a process known as gluconeogenesis .
