He was one of the Islamic world 's leading writers in the field of medicine .
He is remembered in the Western history of medicine as a major historical figure who made important contributions to medicine and the European Renaissance .
His medical texts were unusual in that where controversy existed between Galen and Aristotle 's views on medical matters -LRB- such as anatomy -RRB- , he preferred to side with Aristotle , where necessary updating Aristotle 's position to take into account post-Aristotelian advances in anatomical knowledge .
Aristotle 's dominant intellectual influence among medieval European scholars meant that Avicenna 's linking of Galen 's medical writings with Aristotle 's philosophical writings in the Canon of Medicine -LRB- along with its comprehensive and logical organisation of knowledge -RRB- significantly increased Avicenna 's importance in medieval Europe in comparison to other Islamic writers on medicine .
