In 1620 , a Royal Assent granted Bermuda limited self-governance ; its Parliament is the fifth oldest in the world , behind the Parliament of the United Kingdom , the Tynwald of the Isle of Man , the Althing of Iceland , and Sejm of Poland .
Of these , only Bermuda 's and the Isle of Man 's Tynwald have been in continuous existence since 1620 .
