They also abrade rock and debris from their substrate to create landforms such as cirques and moraines .
Between 35 ° N and 35 ° S , glaciers occur only in the Himalayas , Andes , Rocky Mountains , a few high mountains in East Africa , Mexico , New Guinea and on Zard Kuh in Iran .
Greenland and Patagonia also have huge expanses of continental glaciers .
Glacial ice is the largest reservoir of freshwater on Earth .
Several kilometers deep , they obscure the underlying topography .
Portions of an ice sheet or cap that extend into water are called ice shelves ; they tend to be thin with limited slopes and reduced velocities .
In Antarctica , many ice streams drain into large ice shelves .
Some drain directly into the sea , often with an ice tongue , like Mertz Glacier .
A sub-polar glacier includes both temperate and polar ice , depending on depth beneath the surface and position along the length of the glacier .
A cold-based glacier is below freezing at the ice-ground interface , and is thus frozen to the underlying substrate .
This contrast is thought to a large extent to govern the ability of a glacier to effectively erode its bed , as sliding ice promotes plucking at rock from the surface below .
This snow collects and is compacted by the weight of the snow falling above it forming névé .
Further crushing of the individual snowflakes and squeezing the air from the snow turns it into ` glacial ice ' .
This glacial ice will fill the cirque until it ` overflows ' through a geological weakness or vacancy , such as the gap between two mountains .
When the mass of snow and ice is sufficiently thick , it begins to move due to a combination of surface slope , gravity and pressure .
The upper part of a glacier , where accumulation exceeds ablation , is called the accumulation zone .
Ice in the accumulation zone is deep enough to exert a downward force that erodes underlying rock .
After a glacier melts , it often leaves behind a bowl - or amphitheater-shaped depression that ranges in size from large basins like the Great Lakes to smaller mountain depressions known as cirques .
When a glacier moves through irregular terrain , cracks called crevasses develop in the fracture zone .
If two rigid sections of a glacier move at different speeds and directions , shear forces cause them to break apart , opening a crevasse .
Beneath this point , the plasticity of the ice is too great for cracks to form .
Crevasses can form in several different ways .
Longitudinal crevasses form semi-parallel to flow where a glacier expands laterally .
Marginal crevasses are usually largely transverse to flow .
Moving glacier ice can sometimes separate from stagnant ice above , forming a bergschrund .
These glaciers exhibit normal movement until suddenly they accelerate , then return to their previous state .
During these surges , the glacier may reach velocities far greater than normal speed .
This increase in the numbers of glacial earthquakes in Greenland may be a response to global warming .
This creates a swale and space for snow accumulation in the winter , which in turn creates a ridge .
Extensive glaciers are found in Antarctica , Chile , Canada , Alaska , Greenland and Iceland .
Mainland Australia currently contains no glaciers , although a small glacier on Mount Kosciuszko was present in the last glacial period .
In New Guinea , small , rapidly diminishing , glaciers are located on its highest summit massif of Puncak Jaya .
During glacial periods of the Quaternary , Taiwan , Hawaii on Mauna Kea and Tenerife also had large alpine glaciers , while the Faroe and Crozet Islands were completely glaciated .
Even at high latitudes , glacier formation is not inevitable .
Even during glacial periods of the Quaternary , Manchuria , lowland Siberia , and central and northern Alaska , though extraordinarily cold , had such light snowfall that glaciers could not form .
Glacial abrasion is commonly characterized by glacial striations .
They usually appear as linear mounds of till , a non-sorted mixture of rock , gravel and boulders within a matrix of a fine powdery material .
Terminal or end moraines are formed at the foot or terminal end of a glacier .
The erosion that creates glacial valleys eliminates the spurs of earth that extend across mountain valleys , creating triangular cliffs called truncated spurs .
Within glacial valleys , depressions created by plucking and abrasion can be filled by lakes , called paternoster lakes .
This structure may result in a mountain pass .
The glacier abrades the smooth slope on the upstream side as it flows along , but tears loose and carries away rock from the downstream side via plucking .
After the ice sheet or glacier melts , the mantle begins to flow back to its original position , pushing the crust back up .
That is a very small amount of energy in terms of everyday experience , but everyday experience is not concerned with individual photons any more than with individual atoms or molecules .
It still was not clear why the spectrum of a hot object had the form that it has -LRB- see diagram -RRB- .
The influence of h in this complex factor would not disappear if it were set to zero or to any other value .
They contributed greatly -LRB- along with Einstein 's work on the photoelectric effect -RRB- to convincing physicists that Planck 's postulate of quantized energy levels was more than a mere mathematical formalism .
Another particularly thorough investigation was published by Philipp Lenard in 1902 .
