Other opponents say that affirmative action lowers the bar and so denies those who strive for excellence on their own merit and the sense of real achievement .
This causes reverse discrimination in the form of preferential hirings , contracts , and scholarships as a means to ameliorate past wrongs .
They argue that it hinders reconciliation , replaces old wrongs with new wrongs , undermines the achievements of minorities , and encourages groups to identify themselves as disadvantaged , even if they are not .
Michigan joined California , Florida , Texas , and Washington in banning the use of race or sex in admissions considerations .
Some opponents believe , among other things , that affirmative action devalues the accomplishments of people who belong to a group it 's supposed to help , therefore making affirmative action counter-productive .
Furthermore , opponents of affirmative action claim that these policies dehumanize individuals and applicants to jobs or school are judged as members of a group without consideration for the individual person .
