Matthew 's and Mark 's Gospels record that he refused this .
According to some translations from the original Greek , the thieves may have been bandits or Jewish rebels .
The soldiers affixed a sign above his head stating `` Jesus of Nazareth , King of the Jews '' in three languages , divided his garments and cast lots for his seamless robe .
The Roman soldiers did not break Jesus ' legs , as they did to the other two men crucified -LRB- breaking the legs hastened the crucifixion process -RRB- , as Jesus was dead already .
In the Synoptic Gospels , various supernatural events accompany the crucifixion , including darkness , an earthquake , and -LRB- in Matthew -RRB- the resurrection of saints .
There are several details that are only found in one of the gospel accounts .
The curtain of the Temple is torn in two .
John includes several of the same elements as those found in Mark , though they are treated differently .
However , in John 19:14 Jesus is still before Pilate at the sixth hour .
