Membership in this `` mendicant '' order includes friars , nuns , active sisters , and lay or secular Dominicans -LRB- formerly known as tertiaries , though recently there has been a growing number of Associates , who are unrelated to the tertiaries -RRB- affiliated with the order .
Members of the order generally carry the letters O.P. , standing for Ordinis Praedicatorum , meaning of the Order of Preachers , after their names .
The Dominican Order came into being in the Middle Ages at a time when religion began to be contemplated in a new way .
Instead , they travelled among the people , taking as their examples the apostles of the primitive Church .
They were both active in preaching , and contemplative in study , prayer and meditation .
The brethren of the Dominican Order were urban and learned , as well as contemplative and mystical in their spirituality .
Dominic was fired by a reforming zeal after they encountered Albigensian Christians at Toulouse .
For these reasons , Prior Diego suggested that the papal legates begin to live a reformed apostolic life .
The prior took up the challenge , and he and Dominic dedicated themselves to the conversion of the Albigensians .
The monastery was at Prouille would later become Dominic 's headquarters for his missionary effort there .
When his preaching companions heard of his death , all save Dominic and a very small number of others returned to their homes .
Its purpose was revolutionary in the pastoral ministry of the Catholic Church .
These priests were organized and well trained in religious studies .
Dominic needed a framework -- a rule -- to organize these components .
They could practice ministry and common life while existing in individual poverty .
In Dominic 's thinking , it was impossible for men to preach what they did not or could not understand .
This was the first of many Dominican schools established by the brethren , some near large universities throughout Europe .
Before that time the friars had only a temporary residence in Rome at the convent of San Sisto Vecchio which Honorius III had given to Dominic circa 1218 intending it to become a convent for a reformation of nuns at Rome under Dominic 's guidance .
This studium was transformed into the order 's first studium provinciale by Saint Thomas Aquinas in 1265 .
