This group of skyscrapers was an attempt to keep businesses in downtown .
Young also gave city support to other large developments to attract middle and upper-class residents back to the city .
Major stores and hotels closed and many large office buildings went vacant .
Long a major population center and site of worldwide automobile manufacturing , Detroit has suffered a long economic decline produced by numerous factors .
The city has declined in population in each census since 1950 .
The park has been cited as one of the best public spaces in the United States .
