On June 14 , 2013 Detroit defaulted on $ 2.5 billion of debt by withholding $ 39.7 million in interest payments , while Emergency Manager Kevyn Orr met with bondholders and other creditors in an attempt to restructure the city 's $ 18.5 billion debt and avoid bankruptcy .
