The ancient history of the region includes some of South Asia 's oldest settlements and some of its major civilisations .
Soanian sites are found in the Sivalik region across what are now India , Pakistan , and Nepal .
The civilisation included urban centres such as Dholavira , Kalibangan , Ropar , Rakhigarhi , and Lothal in modern-day India , as well as Harappa , Ganeriwala , and Mohenjo-daro in modern-day Pakistan .
In terms of culture , many regions of the subcontinent transitioned from the Chalcolithic to the Iron Age in this period .
The Kuru state organized the Vedic hymns into collections , and developed the orthodox srauta ritual to uphold the social order .
The archaeological Painted Grey Ware culture , which flourished in the Haryana and western Uttar Pradesh regions of northern India from about 1100 to 600 BCE , is believed to correspond to the Kuru and Panchala kingdoms .
