There is no conclusive proof from archaeology as to whether the specific events of the Mahabharat have any historical basis .
The existing texts of these epics are believed to belong to the post-Vedic age , between c. 400 BCE and 400 CE .
Some even attempted to date the events using methods of archaeoastronomy which have produced , depending on which passages are chosen and how they are interpreted , estimated dates ranging up to mid 2nd millennium BCE .
