By 1957 , pan-Arabism was the dominant ideology of the Arab world , and the average Arab citizen considered Nasser his undisputed leader .
Historian Adeed Dawisha credited Nasser 's status to his `` charisma , bolstered by his perceived victory in the Suez Crisis '' .
