At the time , as opposed to contemporary practice , the participating Cardinals did not have to be below age 80 to vote , there were few Eastern-rite Cardinals , and no Cardinals who were just priests at the time of their elevation .
After the long pontificate of Pope Pius XII , the cardinals chose a man who -- it was presumed because of his advanced age -- would be a short-term or `` stop-gap '' pope .
They wished to choose a candidate who would do little during the new pontificate .
