On 21 December 2011 the bank instituted a programme of making low-interest loans with a term of three years -LRB- 36 months -RRB- and 1 % interest to European banks accepting loans from the portfolio of the banks as collateral .
Loans totalling $ 489.2 bn -LRB- US$ 640 bn -RRB- were announced .
