By the mentioned principle , they are required to respect the group structures in a precise sense .
The structure of groups can also be understood by breaking them into pieces called subgroups and quotient groups .
The principle of `` preserving structures '' -- a recurring topic in mathematics throughout -- is an instance of working in a category , in this case the category of groups .
In many situations it is desirable to consider two group elements the same if they differ by an element of a given subgroup .
