These numbers can be visualized as the vertices on a regular n-gon , as shown in blue at the right for n = 6 .
The group operation is multiplication of complex numbers .
In the picture , multiplying with z corresponds to a counter-clockwise rotation by 60 ° .
Using some field theory , the group Fp × can be shown to be cyclic : for example , if p = 5 , 3 is a generator since 31 = 3 , 32 = 9 ≡ 4 , 33 ≡ 2 , and 34 ≡ 1 .
