In comparison , 19 percent said it was `` too ambitious '' .
Renewables producing electricity accounted for almost half of the 208 GW of capacity added globally during 2011 .
Wind and solar photovoltaics -LRB- PV -RRB- accounted for almost 40 % and 30 % .
This energy consumption is divided as 9 % coming from traditional biomass , 4.2 % as heat energy -LRB- non-biomass -RRB- , 3.8 % hydro electricity and 2 % electricity from wind , solar , geothermal , and biomass .
