Calculations indicate that a zinc compound with the oxidation state of +4 is unlikely to exist .
Otherwise there is little similarity .
Complexes of zinc are mostly 4 - or 6 - coordinate although 5-coordinate complexes are known .
The first zinc -LRB- I -RRB- compound containing the Zn -- Zn bond , -LRB- η5-C5Me5 -RRB- 2Zn2 , is also the first dimetallocene .
Pnictogenides -LRB- Zn 3N 2 , Zn 3P 2 , Zn 3As 2 and Zn 3Sb 2 -RRB- , the peroxide -LRB- ZnO 2 -RRB- , the hydride -LRB- ZnH 2 -RRB- , and the carbide -LRB- ZnC 2 -RRB- are also known .
Of the four halides , ZnF 2 has the most ionic character , whereas the others -LRB- ZnCl 2 , ZnBr 2 , and ZnI 2 -RRB- have relatively low melting points and are considered to have more covalent character .
In weak basic solutions containing Zn2 + ions , the hydroxide Zn -LRB- OH -RRB- 2 forms as a white precipitate .
The nitrate Zn -LRB- NO3 -RRB- 2 , chlorate Zn -LRB- ClO3 -RRB- 2 , sulfate ZnSO 4 , phosphate Zn 3 -LRB- PO4 -RRB- 2 , molybdate ZnMoO 4 , cyanide Zn -LRB- CN -RRB- 2 , arsenite Zn -LRB- AsO2 -RRB- 2 , arsenate Zn -LRB- AsO4 -RRB- 2 · 8H 2O and the chromate ZnCrO 4 -LRB- one of the few colored zinc compounds -RRB- are a few examples of other common inorganic compounds of zinc .
