Southern East Prussia was placed under Polish administration , while northern East Prussia was divided between the Soviet republics of Russia -LRB- the Kaliningrad Oblast -RRB- and Lithuania -LRB- the constituent counties of the Klaipėda Region -RRB- .
Shortly after the end of the war in May 1945 , Germans who had fled in early 1945 tried to return to their homes in East Prussia .
Many more were prevented from returning , -LSB- citation needed -RSB- and the German population of East Prussia was almost completely expelled by the communist regimes .
Subsequently Polish expatriates from Polish lands annexed by the Soviet Union as well as Ukrainians and Lemkos from southern Poland , expelled in Operation Vistula in 1947 , were settled in the southern part of East Prussia , now the Polish Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship .
Local toponyms were Polonised by the Polish Commission for the Determination of Place Names .
In June 1946 114,070 German and 41,029 Soviet citizens were registered in the Oblast , with an unknown number of disregarded unregistered persons .
The last remaining Germans left in November 1949 -LRB- 1,401 persons -RRB- and January 1950 -LRB- 7 persons -RRB- .
A similar fate befell the Curonians who lived in the area around the Curonian Lagoon .
Only 219 lived along the Curonian Spit in 1955 .
Many had German names such as Fritz or Hans , a cause for anti-German discrimination .
The exclave was a military zone , which was closed to foreigners ; Soviet citizens could only enter with special permission .
In 1967 the remnants of Königsberg Castle were demolished on the orders of Leonid Brezhnev to make way for a new `` House of the Soviets '' .
Initially the assemblies of the urban and rural districts elected representatives for the provincial diets -LRB- Provinziallandtage -RRB- , which were thus indirectly elected .
These parliaments legislated within the competences transferred to the provincial associations .
The provincial diet of East Prussia elected a provincial executive body -LRB- government -RRB- , the provincial committee -LRB- Provinzialausschuss -RRB- , and a head of province , the Landeshauptmann -LRB- `` Land Captain '' ; till the 1880s titled Landdirektor , land director -RRB- .
The Ottomans ended the Byzantine Empire with the 1453 conquest of Constantinople by Mehmed the Conqueror .
Some of these were later absorbed into the Ottoman Empire , while others were granted various types of autonomy during the course of centuries .
