The first part of madrasa based education is estimated from the first day of `` nabuwwat '' to the first portion of the `` Umaiya '' caliphate .
-LSB- citation needed -RSB-
Not only was the madrasa a potent symbol of status but it was an effective means of transmitting wealth and status to their descendants .
At the beginning of the Caliphate or Islamic Empire , the reliance on courts initially confined sponsorship and scholarly activities to major centres .
In addition to religious subjects , they also taught the `` rational sciences , '' as varied as mathematics , astronomy , astrology , geography , alchemy , philosophy , magic , and occultism , depending on the curriculum of the specific institution in question .
