In Singapore , madrasahs are private schools which are overseen by Majlis Ugama Islam Singapura -LRB- MUIS , English : Islamic Religious Council of Singapore -RRB- .
Four Madrasahs are coeducational and two are for girls .
Students take a range of Islamic Studies subjects in addition to mainstream MOE curriculum subjects and sit for the PSLE and GCE ` O ' Levels like their peers .
In 2009 , MUIS introduced the `` Joint Madrasah System '' -LRB- JMS -RRB- , a joint collaboration of Madrasah Al-Irsyad Al-Islamiah primary school and secondary schools Madrasah Aljunied Al-Islamiah -LRB- offering the ukhrawi , or religious stream -RRB- and Madrasah Al-Arabiah Al-Islamiah -LRB- offering the academic stream -RRB- .
