Rajasthani cooking was influenced by both the war-like lifestyles of its inhabitants and the availability of ingredients in this arid region .
4 Dal-Bati-Churma is very popular in Rajasthan .
The traditional way to serve it is to first coarsely mash the Baati then pour pure Ghee on top of it .
It is served with the daal -LRB- lentils -RRB- and spicy garlic chutney .
Also served with Besan -LRB- gram flour -RRB- ki kadi .
It is commonly served at all festivities , including religious occasions , wedding ceremonies , and birthday parties in Rajasthan .
`` Dal-Baati-Churma '' , is a combination of three different food items -- Daal -LRB- lentils -RRB- , Baati and Churma -LRB- Sweet -RRB- .
It is a typical Rajasthani dish .
Kathputli , Bhopa , Chang , Teratali , Ghindr , Kachchhighori , and Tejaji are examples of traditional Rajasthani culture .
Rajasthan is known for its traditional , colorful art .
Handicraft items like wooden furniture and crafts , carpets , and blue pottery are commonly found here .
Shopping reflects the colorful culture , Rajasthani clothes have a lot of mirror work and embroidery .
A piece of cloth is used to cover the head , both for protection from heat and maintenance of modesty .
Some of the spirits possessing Rajasthanis are seen as good and beneficial while others are seen as malevolent .
Bad spirits include perpetual debtors who die in debt , stillborn infants , deceased widows , and foreign tourists .
In recent decades , the literacy rate of Rajasthan has increased significantly .
At the Census 2011 , Rajasthan had a literacy rate of 67.06 % -LRB- 80.51 % male and 52.66 % female -RRB- .
Other major educational institutions are Birla Institute of Technology and Science Pilani , Malaviya National Institute of Technology Jaipur , IIM Udaipur r and LNMIIT .
Apart from above there 41 Private universities like Amity University Rajasthan , Jaipur , Manipal University Jaipur , OPJS University , Churu , Mody University of Technology and Science Lakshmangarh -LRB- Women 's University , Sikar -RRB- , RNB Global University , Bikaner .
The state has 23 polytechnic colleges and 152 Industrial Training Institutes -LRB- ITIs -RRB- that impart vocational training .
Tourism is a flourishing industry in Rajasthan .
Many old and neglected palaces and forts have been converted into heritage hotels .
Tourism has increased employment in the hospitality sector .
