The Governor of Guam was federally appointed until 1968 , when the Guam Elective Governor Act provided for the office 's popular election. :242 Since Guam is not a U.S. state , U.S. citizens residing on Guam are not allowed to vote for president and their congressional representative is a non-voting member .
It is the southernmost and largest island in the Mariana island chain and is also the largest island in Micronesia .
Guam is the closest land mass to the Mariana Trench , a deep subduction zone , that lies beside the island chain to the east .
The highest point in Guam is Mount Lamlam at an elevation of 1,334 feet -LRB- 407 meters -RRB- .
In recent years , earthquakes with epicenters near Guam have had magnitudes ranging from 5.0 to 8.7 .
Unlike the Anatahan volcano in the Northern Mariana Islands , Guam is not volcanically active .
The weather is generally very warm and humid with little seasonal temperature variation .
The remaining months -LRB- July to November -RRB- constitute the rainy season .
The highest temperature ever recorded in Guam was 96 °F -LRB- 36 °C -RRB- on April 18 , 1971 and April 1 , 1990 , and the lowest temperature ever recorded was 65 °F -LRB- 18 °C -RRB- on February 8 , 1973 .
Post-European-contact Chamorro culture is a combination of American , Spanish , Filipino , other Micronesian Islander and Mexican traditions , with few remaining indigenous pre-Hispanic customs .
These influences are manifested in the local language , music , dance , sea navigation , cuisine , fishing , games -LRB- such as batu , chonka , estuleks , and bayogu -RRB- , songs and fashion .
Post-contact Chamorro cuisine is largely based on corn , and includes tortillas , tamales , atole and chilaquiles , which are a clear influence from Spanish trade between Mesoamerica and Asia .
Many Chamorros also have Spanish surnames because of their conversion to Roman Catholic Christianity and the adoption of names from the Catálogo alfabético de apellidos , a phenomenon also common to the Philippines .
Chenchule ' is the intricate system of reciprocity at the heart of Chamorro society .
It is rooted in the core value of inafa ` maolek .
Inafa ` maolek , or interdependence , is the key , or central value , in Chamorro culture ... Inafa ` maolek depends on a spirit of cooperation and sharing .
This is the armature , or core , that everything in Chamorro culture revolves around .
It is a powerful concern for mutuality rather than individualism and private property rights . ''
