In Feynman 's own words , `` There was n't anything to do there . ''
Bored , he indulged his curiosity by learning to pick the combination locks on cabinets and desks used to secure papers .
Feynman played many jokes on colleagues .
In one case he found the combination to a locked filing cabinet by trying the numbers he thought a physicist would use -LRB- it proved to be 27 -- 18 -- 28 after the base of natural logarithms , e = 2.71828 ... -RRB- , and found that the three filing cabinets where a colleague kept a set of atomic bomb research notes all had the same combination .
