The first President of Cyprus , Makarios III , was an archbishop .
English was the sole official language during British colonial rule and the lingua franca until 1960 , and continued to be used -LRB- de facto -RRB- in courts of law until 1989 and in legislation until 1996 .
80.4 % of Cypriots are proficient in the English language as a second language .
Russian , after English and Greek , is the third language used on many signs of shops and restaurants , particularly in Limassol and Paphos .
In addition to these languages , 12 % speak French and 5 % speak German .
State schools are generally seen as equivalent in quality of education to private-sector institutions .
Greek Cypriots and Turkish Cypriots share a lot in common in their culture but also have differences .
Hospitality and buying or offering food and drinks for guests or others are common among both .
Greek Cypriots have influences from Greece and Christianity , while Turkish Cypriots have influences from Turkey and Islam .
