Partly due to inefficient generation of electricity in the USSR -LRB- only 20.8 % thermal efficiency in 1950 vs. 36.2 % in 1975 -RRB- , in 1950 diesel traction was about twice as energy efficient as electric traction -LRB- in terms of net tonne-km of freight per kg of fuel -RRB- .
Since energy-intensity is the inverse of energy-efficiency it drops as efficiency goes up .
But most of this 43 % decrease in energy-intensity also benefited diesel traction .
However , there remained a 12 -- 15 % reduction of energy-intensity that only benefited electric traction -LRB- and not diesel -RRB- .
Thus the overall efficiency of electric traction as compared to diesel more than doubled between 1950 and the mid-1970s in the Soviet Union .
