The 1980s ushered in the age of desktop computing .
The new computers empowered their users with spreadsheets like Lotus 1-2-3 and database software like dBASE .
dBASE was one of the top selling software titles in the 1980s and early 1990s .
Programmers and designers began to treat the data in their databases as objects .
That is to say that if a person 's data were in a database , that person 's attributes , such as their address , phone number , and age , were now considered to belong to that person instead of being extraneous data .
This allows for relations between data to be relations to objects and their attributes and not to individual fields .
