In architecture and sculpture , the difference between Greek models and Roman paintings are apparent .
The chief Roman contributions to architecture were the arch and the dome .
Its significance is perhaps best reflected in its endurance and influence , as is seen in the longevity and lasting importance of works of Virgil and Ovid .
Roman law laid the foundations for the laws of many European countries and their colonies .
