The population was 45.3 % non-Hispanic whites , down from 78.9 % in 1970 , 27.7 % Hispanics , 15.6 % Asians/Pacific Islanders , 7.1 % blacks , 0.4 % American Indians , and 3.9 % from other races .
In 2000 , the median income for a household in the city was $ 45,733 , and the median income for a family was $ 53,060 .
The per capita income for the city was $ 23,609 .
