Dialectology within Russia recognizes dozens of smaller-scale variants .
Some of these are relics of ancient usage now completely discarded by the standard language .
Consonants include a fricative / ɣ / , a semivowel / w ~ u̯ / and / x ~ xv ~ xw / , whereas the Standard and Northern dialects have the consonants / ɡ / , / v / , and final / l / and / f / , respectively .
The morphology features a palatalized final / tʲ / in 3rd person forms of verbs -LRB- this is unpalatalized in the Standard and Northern dialects -RRB- .
