Promotions among enlisted personnel and non-commissioned officers are generally designated by increasing numbers of insignia chevrons .
-LSB- citation needed -RSB-
The promotion from first lieutenant to captain is competitive after successfully completing another two years of service , with a selection rate varying between 99 % and 100 % .
At the 10 to 11 year mark , captains will take part in a selection board to major .
If not selected , they will meet a follow-on board to determine if they will be allowed to remain in the Air Force .
Most of the existing Air Force warrant officers entered the commissioned officer ranks during the 1960s , but small numbers continued to exist in the warrant officer grades for the next 21 years .
While all USAF military personnel are referred to as Airmen , the term also refers to the pay grades of E-1 through E-4 , which are below the level of non-commissioned officers -LRB- NCOs -RRB- .
The Air Force mirrored the Army from 1976 to 1991 with an E-4 being either a Senior Airman wearing three stripes without a star or a Sergeant -LRB- referred to as `` Buck Sergeant '' -RRB- , which was noted by the presence of the central star and considered an NCO .
This is worn with a light blue shirt -LRB- Shade 1550 -RRB- and Shade 1620 herringbone patterned necktie .
USAF personnel assigned to Base Honor Guard duties wear , for certain occasions , a modified version of the standard service dress uniform , but with silver trim on the sleeves and trousers , with the addition of a ceremonial belt -LRB- if necessary -RRB- , wheel cap with silver trim and Hap Arnold Device , and a silver aiguillette placed on the left shoulder seam and all devices and accoutrement .
Over time , various badges have been discontinued and are no longer distributed .
The annual ergo-cycle test which the USAF had used for several years had been replaced in 2004 .
Airmen can potentially earn a score of 100 , with the run counting as 60 % , waist circumference as 20 % , and both strength test counting as 10 % each .
Effective 1 July 2010 , the AFFT is administered by the base Fitness Assessment Cell -LRB- FAC -RRB- , and is required twice a year .
Additionally , only meeting the minimum standards on each one of these tests will not get you a passing score of 75 % , and failing any one component will result in a failure for the entire test .
In the US Air Force , the distinction between bombers , fighters that are actually fighter-bombers , and attack aircraft has become blurred .
Many fighter aircraft , such as the F-16 , are often used as ` bomb trucks ' , despite being designed for aerial combat .
The B-52 Stratofortress airframe design is over 60 years old and the B-52H aircraft currently in the active inventory were all built between 1960 and 1962 .
These aircraft are largely defined in terms of their range capability as strategic airlift -LRB- C-5 -RRB- , strategic/tactical -LRB- C-17 -RRB- , and tactical -LRB- C-130 -RRB- airlift to reflect the needs of the land forces they most often support .
It conducts long-range , special operations missions , and is equipped with extra fuel tanks and terrain-following radar .
Other missions include interception of bombers and other fighters , reconnaissance , and patrol .
The USAF has 2,025 fighters in service as of September 2012 .
This makes these aircraft an essential part of the Air Force 's global mobility and the U.S. force projection .
Daniel L. Magruder , Jr defines USAF culture as a combination of the rigorous application of advanced technology , individualism and progressive airpower theory .
Air Force officers have never felt they needed the formal social `` distance '' from their enlisted force that is common in the other U.S. armed services .
When the enlisted force did go into harm 's way , such as members of multi-crewed aircraft , the close comradeship of shared risk in tight quarters created traditions that shaped a somewhat different kind of officer/enlisted relationship than exists elsewhere in the military .
