This setup presaged the use of LEDs for optical communication applications .
By October 1961 , they had demonstrated efficient light emission and signal coupling between a GaAs p-n junction light emitter and an electrically-isolated semiconductor photodetector .
In October 1962 , TI announced the first LED commercial product -LRB- the SNX-100 -RRB- , which employed a pure GaAs crystal to emit a 890 nm light output .
In October 1963 , TI announced the first commercial hemispherical LED , the SNX-110 .
Holonyak first reported his LED in the journal Applied Physics Letters on the December 1 , 1962 .
In 1976 , T. P. Pearsall created the first high-brightness , high-efficiency LEDs for optical fiber telecommunications by inventing new semiconductor materials specifically adapted to optical fiber transmission wavelengths .
The Monsanto Company was the first organization to mass-produce visible LEDs , using gallium arsenide phosphide -LRB- GaAsP -RRB- in 1968 to produce red LEDs suitable for indicators .
These red LEDs were bright enough only for use as indicators , as the light output was not enough to illuminate an area .
Later , other colors became widely available and appeared in appliances and equipment .
These devices employed compound semiconductor chips fabricated with the planar process invented by Dr. Jean Hoerni at Fairchild Semiconductor .
The combination of planar processing for chip fabrication and innovative packaging methods enabled the team at Fairchild led by optoelectronics pioneer Thomas Brandt to achieve the needed cost reductions .
These methods continue to be used by LED producers .
In parallel , Isamu Akasaki and Hiroshi Amano in Nagoya were working on developing the important GaN nucleation on sapphire substrates and the demonstration of p-type doping of GaN .
The combination of that yellow with remaining blue light appears white to the eye .
However using different phosphors -LRB- fluorescent materials -RRB- it also became possible to instead produce green and red light through fluorescence .
The resulting mixture of red , green and blue is not only perceived by humans as white light but is superior for illumination in terms of color rendering , whereas one can not appreciate the color of red or green objects illuminated only by the yellow -LRB- and remaining blue -RRB- wavelengths from the YAG phosphor .
