The Roman synagogue in Ein Gedi was remodeled in the Byzantine era and a more elaborate mosaic floor was laid down above the older white panels .
The usual geometric design was enriched with birds in the center .
A further portion of the floor was divided by medallions formed by vine leaves , each of which contains an animal : a lioness suckling her cub , a giraffe , peacocks , panthers , bears , a zebra and so on .
It is very similar to that of the synagogue at Maon -LRB- Menois -RRB- and the Christian church at Shellal , suggesting that the same artist most probably worked at all three places .
