Between the federal and civic buildings on the Monumental Axis is the city 's cathedral , considered by many to be Niemeyer 's finest achievement -LRB- see photographs of the interior -RRB- .
The parabolically shaped structure is characterized by its 16 gracefully curving supports , which join in a circle 115 feet -LRB- 35 meters -RRB- above the floor of the nave ; stretched between the supports are translucent walls of tinted glass .
The nave is entered via a subterranean passage rather than conventional doorways .
