The religion has been criticized for its `` two witness rule '' for church discipline , based on its application of scriptures at Deuteronomy 19:15 and Matthew 18:15 -17 , which requires sexual abuse to be substantiated by secondary evidence if the accused person denies any wrongdoing .
A former member of the church 's headquarters staff , Barbara Anderson , says the policy effectively requires that there be another witness to an act of molestation , `` which is an impossibility '' .
The Watch Tower Society 's policy is that elders inform authorities when required by law to do so , but otherwise leave that action up to the victim and his or her family .
