In addition there are at present no bag limits and the open season is comparatively very long -LRB- 5 months - October to February inclusive -RRB- .
As a result , the populations of the five major mammalian game species -LRB- red-rumped agouti , lowland paca , nine-banded armadillo , collared peccary , and red brocket deer -RRB- are thought to be quite low -LRB- although scientifically conducted population studies are only just recently being conducted as of 2013 -RRB- .
Various herons , ducks , doves , the green iguana , the gold tegu , the spectacled caiman and the common opossum are also commonly hunted and poached .
There is also some poaching of ` fully protected species ' , including red howler monkeys and capuchin monkeys , southern tamanduas , Brazilian porcupines , yellow-footed tortoises , Trinidad piping guans and even one of the national birds , the scarlet ibis .
There is presumed to be relatively very little subsistence hunting in the country -LRB- with most hunting for either sport or commercial profit -RRB- .
The local wildlife management authority is under-staffed and under-funded , and as such very little in the way of enforcement is done to uphold existing wildlife management laws , with hunting occurring both in and out of season , and even in wildlife sanctuaries .
There is some indication that the government is beginning to take the issue of wildlife management more seriously , with well drafted legislation being brought before Parliament in 2015 .
It remains to be seen if the drafted legislation will be fully adopted and financially supported by the current and future governments , and if the general populace will move towards a greater awareness of the importance of wildlife conservation and change the culture of wanton consumption to one of sustainable management .
