Of these , Kathmandu Valley is in the Warm Temperate Zone -LRB- elevation ranging from 1,200 -- 2,300 metres -LRB- 3,900 -- 7,500 ft -RRB- -RRB- , where the climate is fairly temperate , atypical for the region .
In the Kathmandu Valley , which is representative of its valley 's climate , the average summer temperature varies from 28 -- 30 °C -LRB- 82 -- 86 °F -RRB- .
Unpredictable weather is expected , given that temperatures can drop to 1 °C -LRB- 34 °F -RRB- or less during the winter .
Rainfall has been recorded at about 1,400 millimetres -LRB- 55.1 in -RRB- for the Kathmandu valley , and averages 1,407 millimetres -LRB- 55.4 in -RRB- for the city of Kathmandu .
On average humidity is 75 % .
